text: Shahid Talebi Dam is a hydroelectric dam in Iran with an installed electricity generating capability of 2.3 MWh.http://en.iwpco.ir/default.aspx It is situated in town of Sepidan in Fars Province and first came online in 1994, after three years of construction.http://www.tavanir.org.ir/info/stat80/future.htm ==See also== *List of power stations in Iran ==References== Category:Dams in Iran Category:Dams completed in 1994 Category:Buildings and structures in Fars Province
title: Shahid Talebi Dam
